properties.name: Brandenburg Gate
properties.attractiondescrip: The Brandenburg Gate is an 18th-century neoclassical monument in Berlin, built on the orders of Prussian king Frederick William II after the temporary restoration of order during the Batavian Revolution

properties.name: Fortress Hohensalzburg
properties.attractiondescrip: Erected at the behest of the Prince-Archbishops of Salzburg with a length of 250 m and a width of 150 m, it is one of the largest medieval castles in Europe. Hohensalzburg Fortress is situated at an altitude of 506 m

properties.name: Karlštejn Castle
properties.attractiondescrip: Karlštejn Castle is a large Gothic castle founded 1348 by Charles IV, Holy Roman Emperor-elect and King of Bohemia. The castle served as a place for safekeeping the Imperial Regalia as well as the Bohemian/Czech crown jewels, holy relics, and other royal treasures.

properties.name: Schönbrunn Palace
properties.attractiondescrip: The 1,441-room Rococo palace is one of the most important architectural, cultural, and historic monuments in the country. Since the mid-1950s it has been a major tourist attraction.

properties.name: Charles Bridge
properties.attractiondescrip: Charles Bridge is a historic bridge that crosses the Vltava river in Prague, Czech Republic. Its construction started in 1357 under the auspices of King Charles IV, and finished in the beginning of the 15th century.

properties.name: Tivoli
properties.attractiondescrip: Tivoli, also known as Tivoli Gardens, is an amusement park and pleasure garden in Copenhagen, Denmark. The park opened on 15 August 1843 and is the second-oldest operating amusement park in the world, after Dyrehavsbakken in nearby Klampenborg, also in Denmark. With 4.6 million visitors in 2017, Tivoli is the second-most popular seasonal amusement park in the world after Europa-Park.
properties.tags: Tivoli, Family, Denmark, Copenhagen, Amusement Park, Garden

properties.name: LEGOLAND
properties.attractiondescrip: LEGOLAND ApS operates an amusement park for families and children in Denmark. Its amenities include a resort, a hotel, activities, shops, and food and drinks. The company was founded in 1968 and is based in Billund, Denmark. As of August 16, 2005, LEGOLAND ApS operates as a subsidiary of Merlin Entertainments plc.
properties.tags: Legoland, Denmark, Copenhagen, family, amusement park
